          <text>
            <![CDATA[ <p><strong>Connecting Communities Post Disasters Act of 2021</strong> </p> <p>This bill requires the Federal Communications Commission to exempt projects that replace or make improvements to communications facilities&nbsp;following a presidentially declared &nbsp;major disaster or emergency from certain environmental or historic preservation review requirements.</p> <p>Specifically, the bill exempts such projects from&nbsp;any requirement to prepare an environmental assessment or environmental impact statement. Such projects are also exempt from considerations about the effect they will have on any historic property.</p>]]>
          </text>
          <updateDate>2021-03-18T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <name>Introduced in Senate</name>
        </item>
